Texture comment: Fresh plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomero-porphyritic dacitic rock (pebbles) or lava. Fine-grained volcanic origin xenolith (up tp 7 mm) in the groundmass. Highly vesiculated. Vesicles are elongated and oriented. Seawater-origin halite precipitated in the tiny cracks. One lighter gray clast in rubble bin between 45-50 cm
Groundmass comments: Quenched glass lines on the outer surface and surface of vesicle, and variable size of xenolith.
Phenocryst 1 comments: some present in clots of plagioclase with pyroxene.
Vesicle comments: 15% of very elongated and oriented sub-rounded vesicles.

Texture comment: Flow texture in fresh plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomero-porphyritic dacitic rock (pebble) or lava. Seawater-origin halite precipitated in the tiny cracks.
Groundmass comments: Massive, micro- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very small vesicles; Some gray precipitate/coating at outer surface
Phenocryst 1 comments: some present in clots of plagioclase with pyroxene.
Vesicle comments: About 7 vol.% of very small vesicles, partly spherical but most show elongated flow texture
